      • setTrafficTag

        public VifAttachmentContext.Builder setTrafficTag(Long trafficTag)
        Current we use VLAN id as the traffic tag. Only effective when vif_type is CHILD. Each logical port inside a container must have a unique traffic tag. If the traffic_tag is not unique, no error is generated, but traffic will not be delivered to any port with a non-unique tag. format: int32
        Parameters:
        trafficTag - New value for the property.

      • setTransportNodeUuid

        public VifAttachmentContext.Builder setTransportNodeUuid(String transportNodeUuid)
        Only effective when vif_type is INDEPENDENT. Each logical port inside a bare metal server or container must have a transport node UUID. We use transport node ID as transport node UUID.
        Parameters:
        transportNodeUuid - New value for the property.
